The paper proposes a differentiable rendering framework for inferring 3D information from 2D images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves graphics rendering and mesh processing, which are also relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the use of back-propagation and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image representations, including silhouette and shading, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
